<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Understanding the 4Ps of Business</h1>
        <div class="section">
            <h2>1. Product</h2>
            <p>The product is what a business sells. It must meet customer needs and be designed effectively.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="section">
            <h2>2. Price</h2>
            <p>Price refers to how much a business charges for its product. Strategies include cost-plus, penetration pricing, and price skimming.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="section">
            <h2>3. Place</h2>
            <p>Place involves how the product reaches the customer, such as direct selling, retail, or e-commerce.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="section">
            <h2>4. Promotion</h2>
            <p>Promotion includes advertising, sales promotions, and PR to attract customers.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
